US-008 is complete. Here's the summary:

**What shipped**
- `iterations/digital_lexicon_v30.html`: append-only US-008 block (~245 lines) ‚Äî a `<style>` rule for `mark.v30-verbatim-mark` (yellow background) plus an IIFE that wraps `window.updateDrawerContent` and, after the v29 article-render runs, finds the cell's `verbatim` text inside each `.v29-art-body` and wraps every contiguous match in a `<mark>`. First mark gets `scrollIntoView({block:'center'})`. Old marks are stripped via `_clearMarks` before applying new ones. Lenient against smart quotes, NBSP / soft hyphen / BOM, en/em dash, whitespace runs and case. No new inline `onclick=` handlers ‚Äî wired purely via the function-wrap pattern.
- `iterations/test_lexicon_v30.py` (new): 13 structural tests covering append-only contract, no-new-onclick guarantee, mark class + yellow background, helper presence, clear-before-apply ordering, normalization coverage of required lenient cases, and trailing-script verification.

**Validation**
- `pytest iterations/test_lexicon_v30.py` ‚Äî 13/13 pass.
